title: Um... guys?
body:
I just realised something.

You know how “Killing Eve” is based on Luke Jenning’s Villanelle series? 
And you know how Jennings originally published the series in 2014?
And you remember all the drama that played out at the Bolshoi in 2013?
And you know how Jennings is a former dance critic?
And you know how Villannelle’s real last name is Astankova in the TV series?
Except that it’s actually Vorontsova in the books?

Did Jennings name his serial killer character after Angelina Vorontsova? Because that’s what I would call a d*ck move.

d i s c l a i m e r

summary: I believe she has traumatized childhood. I remember some episode mentioned that her father was a drunk and Villanelle said her...
body:
My two cents about Villanelle’s mental trauma

I believe she has traumatized childhood. I remember some episode mentioned that her father was a drunk and Villanelle said her mom had really thin shitty hair in ep 2. That’s what I think her parents affected her somehow. She was probably sexual abused by her drunken father while her mother did nothing to help her. So, “really thin shitty hair” isn’t her role model, also isn’t what she looks for a woman she would love. And that’s probably why she chops knobs off. She attacked her school mate when she was 8, so she must have seen or learnt domestic violence long before that. Like @villanever​ said “she never grows up”, and I totally agree with that. Her childhood stopped there at the age of 7-8. I believe no one born as an evil except they’re the omen, Satan’s children or some shit like that. Villlanelle must have been severely abused by her parents somehow until her mental health was distorted to something as close as a psychopath.

For “She has no feeling, emotions, or sympathy ” stuff, I disagree. She has many emotions that she has been practicing so hard to hide them. She has feelings for Eve. She helps her cellmate to avoid facing death by telling the women to look at her before she was shot. She truly cares for Konstantin. She likes Irina, I think she even envies the girl for being loved so much by her father, unlike hers. She never felt loved until she met Anna. And when Anna killed herself, look at her surprising, tearing up, sad face. She did feel sad for her first love’s death even though it was for a few seconds. Another person she (used to) love died. I think if she didn’t have feelings for Eve already, she might even let those tears she was holding up fall.

It makes me wonder how emotional Villanelle would be if Eve hurt herself because she knows she’s Villanelle’s kryptonite. If Eve could cut her leg to see how the blood run, I have no doubt she would be able to hurt herself again when her darkness possesses her just to hurt Villanelle.

Better stop here. I don’t know how to write good theories. LOL.
